content.text:
Successfully implemented mobile responsive behavior for collapsible containers!

## **Key Fix Applied:**

**ğŸ” Root Cause**: MediaWiki's responsive system adds `body.skin--responsive` class on narrow screens, which overrides all floating elements to `float: none`, but our containers weren't inheriting this behavior.

**ğŸ“± Mobile Override Rules Added:**
```css
@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Override all floating containers to be non-floating on mobile */
    .collapsible-container:has([class*="floatright"], [class*="-right"], .infobox:not(.skill-info), etc.) {
        float: none !important;
        clear: both !important; 
        margin: 1em auto !important; /* Center on mobile like web */
    }
}
```

**ğŸ¯ Expected Behavior:**
- **Wide screens**: Infoboxes float right (unchanged)
- **Narrow screens (<768px)**: Infoboxes become centered/non-floating (now matches web)

This replicates MediaWiki's `body.skin--responsive` system behavior, ensuring perfect consistency between app and web across all screen sizes. Main infoboxes will now center on mobile devices just like the web version.

